    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `FlashAttentionForwardSm120`, a thin subclass of `FlashAttentionForwardSm80` that overrides `can_implement()` with SM120's 99 KB SMEM capacity check\n- Wire SM120 dispatch into `interface.py` with SM120-tuned tile sizes and SM80-compatible argument ordering\n- Fix an SM80 causal softmax bug in `flash_fwd.py` that was exposed by SM120 testing (see below)\n\nSM120 (Blackwell GeForce / DGX Spark) uses the same SM80-era MMA instructions (`mma.sync.aligned.m16n8k16`) but has 99 KB shared memory vs 163 KB on SM80 and 228 KB on datacenter Blackwell. No tcgen05, no WGMMA, no TMEM — but does have TMA (not used in this PR).\n\n### SM80 causal bug fix (first commit, can be cherry-picked independently)\n\nThe causal masking loop in `FlashAttentionForwardSm80.kernel()` passed `is_first_n_block=True` to `compute_one_n_block` for all causal iterations. This caused `online_softmax` to reset the running max/sum on each iteration, producing incorrect output when there are 2+ causal N-blocks (D>64 with tile_n=64). The SM90 kernel's causal section correctly omits `is_first_n_block` (defaults to `False`). This was a regression from the SM80 refactor that split SM90 into its own file.\n\n### Tile sizes\n\n| head_dim | tile_m x tile_n | SMEM usage | Notes |\n|----------|----------------|------------|-------|\n| ≤64 | 128×128 | 48 KB | Good occupancy |\n| >64 | 128×64 | 64 KB | 128×128 would use 96 KB |\n\n### Argument ordering\n\nSM80 `__call__` takes `(stream, softmax_scale)` while SM90/SM100/SM110 take `(softmax_scale, stream)`. SM80 also requires `Optional[Float32]` for softmax_scale. The dispatch handles this via conditional argument swapping.\n\n## Limitations (future PRs)\n\n- No SplitKV (flash decoding)\n- No paged KV cache\n- No varlen sequences\n- No backward pass\n- No TMA optimization\n\n## Test plan\n\nValidated on NVIDIA GB10 (DGX Spark, SM121a) — 17/17 configs pass:\n\n```\nGPU: NVIDIA GB10\nCompute capability: (12, 1)\n\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=64  causal=False: max_diff=0.003906\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=64  causal=True:  max_diff=0.007812\nPASS B=1 Sq=512 Sk=512 H=4 D=64  causal=False: max_diff=0.001953\nPASS B=1 Sq=512 Sk=512 H=4 D=64  causal=True:  max_diff=0.007812\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=96  causal=False: max_diff=0.003906\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=96  causal=True:  max_diff=0.015625\nPASS B=1 Sq=512 Sk=512 H=4 D=96  causal=False: max_diff=0.001953\nPASS B=1 Sq=512 Sk=512 H=4 D=96  causal=True:  max_diff=0.015625\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=128 causal=False: max_diff=0.003906\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=128 causal=True:  max_diff=0.015625\nPASS B=4 Sq=128 Sk=128 H=16 D=128 causal=False: max_diff=0.007812\nPASS B=1 Sq=1024 Sk=1024 H=8 D=128 causal=False: max_diff=0.000977\nPASS B=1 Sq=1024 Sk=1024 H=8 D=128 causal=True:  max_diff=0.007812\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=128 causal=False: max_diff=0.003906\nPASS B=2 Sq=256 Sk=256 H=8 D=128 causal=True:  max_diff=0.015625\nPASS B=1 Sq=2048 Sk=2048 H=4 D=128 causal=False: max_diff=0.000977\nPASS B=1 Sq=2048 Sk=2048 H=4 D=128 causal=True:  max_diff=0.007812\n```\n\nAll max_diff values < 0.016 vs PyTorch reference.\n\nContributed by Second Nature Computing (https://joinsecondnature.com)\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
